OL,3,CBristol Airport takes legal action
OL,4,Cover #205m Cardiff investment
OL,6,FBristol Airport has launched legal
OL,7,Faction against the Welsh Government
OL,8,Ffor providing Cardiff Airport with a
OL,9,F#205.2 million subsidy package,
OL,10,Fdelivered over 10 years.
OL,12,FThe Cabinet Secretary for Economy,
OL,13,FRebecca Evans, published a statement
OL,14,Fon Wednesday, 9July that said the
OL,15,Fgovernment had received notice of
OL,16,Flegal action on 25 June.
OL,18,FShe said: "Bristol Airport is
OL,19,Fchallenging the decision of the Welsh
OL,20,FMinisters by way of an appeal to the
OL,21,FCompetition Appeal Tribunal (CAT)...
