OL,3,CBristol Airport takes legal action
OL,4,Cover #205m Cardiff investment
OL,6,FReacting to the news of legal action,
OL,7,Fthe Welsh Conservatives have renewed
OL,8,Fcriticism of Labour's spending.
OL,10,FShadow Cabinet Secretary for
OL,11,FTransport, Sam Rowlands, said: "The
OL,12,FWelsh Labour Government has already
OL,13,Fsunk more than #200 million of
OL,14,Ftaxpayers' money into this failing
OL,15,Fnationalised airport - that's around
OL,16,F#286 per household across Wales.
OL,18,F"Given these figures, people across
OL,19,FWales will rightly question what they
OL,20,Fare getting in return.
