OL,3,CBristol Airport takes legal action
OL,4,Cover #205m Cardiff investment
OL,6,FA spokesperson for Bristol Airport
OL,7,Fsaid: "Unfortunately, the Welsh
OL,8,FGovernment failed to respond to
OL,9,Frepeated requests for more information
OL,10,Fand to engage meaningfully with us and
OL,11,Fother stakeholders for many months
OL,12,Fbefore confirming this unprecedented
OL,13,Fsubsidy of #205m, far beyond the #20m
OL,14,Fannounced publicly on 2April.
OL,16,F"We have therefore sought a review by
OL,17,Fthe Competition Appeal Tribunal under
OL,18,Fthe Subsidy Control Act."
